      <div>
        <h2><span id="power"> &nbsp; </span>Power Measurement Engineer</h2>
          <p>At <%= link_to "Broadcom", "http://www.broadcom.com/", :target => "_blank" %>, I worked as a developer supporting the Power Management Team for 8 months from May to December 2012. I was responsible for measuring the power consumption of system-on-chip devices as the firmware evolved, and as new chipsets came out.</p>

          <p>In order to create reproducible results, I wrote low-level driver scripts to replicate user behaviour (such as playing Angry Birds). It was also necessary to create physical test harnesses to accurately measure power consumption during use-cases such as video recording.</p>

          <p>Being the most familiar with the measurement setups, I debugged power regressions as new software came out. Debugging some of these issues would prove incredibly complex, requiring measurements taken in multiple hardware configurations to find the root cause of the issue. In situations like these, documentation on the wiki, on JIRA, and engineering logbooks proved vital to solving issues.</p>
