      <div>
        <h2><span id="image"> &nbsp; </span>Image Analysis Algorithm Developer</h2>
          <p>In 2011, I worked as a software developer at <%= link_to "Taiheiyo Cement", "http://www.taiheiyo-cement.co.jp/english/", :target => "_blank" %> from May to December as part of the Canada Japan Co-op Program. My role was to provide programming expertise for the Cement Chemistry team, helping them to quantify their cement samples using image analysis algorithms.<p>

          <p>In the first few months, I assessed my coworkers needs, and built prototype scripts in Scilab. The team decided they would like to examine multiple types of cement in various ways, and I decided that building an image analysis toolkit would be best. I then architected an application using Windows Presentation Foundation for the interface, and OpenCV as the processing backend.</p>

          <p>After reading cement analysis research papers, it became obvious I would have to invent the analysis algorithms myself. At that point, programming the entire analysis framework myself would take too long, and I decided that coming up with algorithms using off-the-shelf analysis solutions would deliver the best results for the team.</p>

          <p>After more research, which included preparing my own cement samples and taking pictures with electron microscopes, I was able to use a sequence of ImageJ operations to come up with two successful algorithms.</p>

